## <a id='prereqs'></a>Prerequisites

To complete this tutorial, you will need:

- An [Amazon Web Services](http://aws.amazon.com) (AWS) account with Virtual Private Cloud (VPC).

- The [AWS CLI](https://aws.amazon.com/cli/) installed on your machine.

<p class='note'><strong>Note</strong>: If you have trouble installing the AWS CLI on Linux, OS X, or Unix using pip or the bundled installer, as described the AWS CLI [User Guide](http://http://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/installing.html), try installing the awscli package using [Homebrew](http://brew.sh/).

- Basic familiarity with [BOSH](https://bosh.io/), a tool that deploys and manages distributed software systems.

- The [BOSH CLI](https://bosh.io/docs/bosh-cli.html) and [bosh-init](https://bosh.io/docs/install-bosh-init.html) installed on your machine.

## <a id='procs'></a>Overview: BOSH and Ops Manager
Ops Manager is a graphical front-end to BOSH. When you use Ops Manager to deploy a software product, Ops Manager directs BOSH to run the deployment on the back end.

Because Ops Manager adds an additional layer of complexity to the deployment process, tile authors should first confirm that their product deploys successfully with BOSH alone. Once their BOSH deployment works, the authors can then add the necessary pieces to turn their product into a click-deployable tile for Ops Manager. This tutorial follows these two steps:

1. [Deploying A PCF Product Using BOSH](./deploying-with-bosh.html) describes how to deploy a software product with BOSH, step by step, using a simple example. You should confirm that a BOSH deployment succeeds with your product before you try to deploy it via Ops Manager.

1. [Deploying Your Product as a Tile in Ops Manager](./deploying-with-ops-man-tile.html) explains how to create a tile that packages your product and deploys it through Ops Manager.

## <a id='ref-docs'></a>Reference Documentation

Ops Manager product tiles generate a BOSH manifest, the document that configures and directs the product's deployment. The [Product Template Reference](./product-template-reference.html) explains the key-value pairs that this BOSH manifest must contain.
